SEXY budding model Lerato Makgatho could not contain her excitement upon discovering she was our SunBabe of the Month.&nbsp;So happy was the 24-year-old from Tshwane, she began contemplating the world of opportunities her SunBabe victory would unlock.Said Lerato: &ldquo;I don&rsquo;t believe what I&rsquo;m hearing, you just made my day. I&rsquo;ve been entering competitions since I started my modelling career. This victory gives me confidence to consider pageants such as Miss South Africa.&rdquo;This fine lass &ndash; who looks up to one of Mzansi&rsquo;s most popular professional models, the sultry Babalwa Mneno &ndash; found her way into modelling in the year 2000, at the age of seven, when she entered Miss Winterveld and Miss Mabopane.&nbsp;&ldquo;Babalwa inspires me as she takes her work seriously and never disappoints,&rdquo; Lerato said.&nbsp;&ldquo;I wish to be like her one day. She makes confidence look sexy and has a good business head on her shoulders.&rdquo;Lerato said her SunBabe victory was the boost her career needed.&ldquo;Sunday Sun is a great platform, I&rsquo;m truly honoured!&rdquo;&nbsp;